('BIO 2129', 'Human Anatomy and Physiology', 'Studies the structure and function of the human organism. Includes cells and tissues, skeletal, integumentary, muscular, and nervous systems. Includes laboratory. Credit will not be given for both BIO 2129 and BIO 4410.  Typically offered: Autumn, Summer.   Fee(s): Biology Laboratory Fee', 5, 'WKAS', NULL, NULL, '[[[{"course_id": "CHM 1100", "min_grade": "C-", "concurrent_available": false}], [{"course_id": "CHM 1211", "min_grade": "C-", "concurrent_available": false}], [{"course_id": "CHM 1310", "min_grade": "C-", "concurrent_available": false}], [{"course_id": "Chemistry Proficiency Exam", "min_grade": "35", "concurrent_available": false}]]]', '["BIO 2129L"]', 0),
