('BIO 3325', 'Genetics', 'Introduces inheritance of specific traits through the study of transmission genetics. Focuses on the biology of gene transmission, nucleic acids, chromosome structure, regulation, epigenetics, genetic disease, and biotechnology. Research methods are stressed throughout the course.   Fee(s): Biology Laboratory Fee', 5, 'UD', NULL, '{"excluded_fields": null, "allowed_fields": ["Applied Human Biology", "Biochemistry", "Biology", "Cellular and Molecular Biology", "Chemistry", "Ecology", "Life Science", "Physiology"], "transfer_only": false}', '[[[{"course_id": "BIO 2101", "min_grade": "C-", "concurrent_available": false}]], [[{"course_id": "MAT 2360", "min_grade": "C-", "concurrent_available": false}], [{"course_id": "MAT 1235", "min_grade": "C-", "concurrent_available": false}]]]', NULL, 0),
('BIO 3325L', 'Genetics Lab', 'Lab Component of BIO 3325.', NULL, 'UD', NULL, NULL, NULL, '["BIO 3325"]', 0),
('BIO 3350', 'Immunology', 'Covers major features of innate and adaptive immunity including: Antibodies, T cell receptors, leukocyte development, responses to bacterial and viral infections, vaccines, and disorders of the immune system such as allergy, autoimmunity, and AIDS.', 3, 'UD', 'senior,junior,graduate,post-baccalaureate,doctoral,sophomore', NULL, '[[[{"course_id": "BIO 2101", "min_grade": "C-", "concurrent_available": false}], [{"course_id": "BIO 2129", "min_grade": "C-", "concurrent_available": false}, {"course_id": "BIO 2130", "min_grade": "C-", "concurrent_available": false}]]]', NULL, 0),
('BIO 3351', 'General Microbiology', 'Clinically focused overview of the field of microbiology with an emphasis on the bacterial, viral and fungal organisms that cause disease in humans. Required laboratory focuses on the appropriate handling, growth, and identification of microorganisms in clinical applications.   Fee(s): Biology Laboratory Fee', 5, 'UD', NULL, NULL, '[[[{"course_id": "BIO 2101", "min_grade": "C-", "concurrent_available": false}], [{"course_id": "BIO 2129", "min_grade": "C-", "concurrent_available": false}, {"course_id": "BIO 2130", "min_grade": "C-", "concurrent_available": false}], [{"course_id": "BIO 2571", "min_grade": "C-", "concurrent_available": false}]]]', NULL, 0),
('BIO 3351L', 'General Microbiology Lab', 'Lab Component of BIO 3351.', NULL, 'UD', NULL, NULL, NULL, '["BIO 3351"]', 0),
('BIO 3432', 'Biodiversity: Vertebrate Biology', 'Examines vertebrate life in an evolutionary context through the study of adaptations, comparative anatomy, paleontology, and natural history. Includes laboratory.   Fee(s): Biology Laboratory Fee', 5, 'UD', NULL, NULL, '[[[{"course_id": "BIO 2102", "min_grade": "C-", "concurrent_available": false}, {"course_id": "BIO 2103", "min_grade": "C-", "concurrent_available": false}], [{"course_id": "BIO 2571", "min_grade": "C-", "concurrent_available": false}]]]', NULL, 0),
('BIO 3432L', 'Biodiversity: Vertebrate Biology Lab', 'Lab Component of BIO 3432.', NULL, 'UD', NULL, NULL, NULL, '["BIO 3432"]', 0),
('BIO 3453', 'Biodiversity: Plant Identification and Taxonomy', 'Explores sampling, identification, and systematics of the major plant families with special emphasis on the flora of the Pacific Northwest. Includes laboratory/field studies.  Typically offered: Spring.   Fee(s): Biology Laboratory Fee', 5, 'UD', NULL, NULL, '[[[{"course_id": "BIO 2103", "min_grade": "C-", "concurrent_available": false}], [{"course_id": "BIO 2571", "min_grade": "C-", "concurrent_available": false}]]]', '["BIO 3453L", "BIO 3453F"]', 0),
('BIO 3453F', 'Biodiversity: Plant Identification and Taxonomy-Field Experience', 'Field experience for BIO 3453.   Fee(s): Blakely/NMS Course Fee', NULL, 'UD', NULL, NULL, NULL, '["BIO 3453"]', 0),
('BIO 3453L', 'Biodiversity: Plant Identification and Taxonomy Lab', 'Lab Component of BIO 3453.', NULL, 'UD', NULL, NULL, NULL, '["BIO 3453"]', 0),
('BIO 3615', 'Issues and Values in Biology', 'Examines ethical issues in biology and medicine that help shape a Christian worldview and value system. This immersive seminar-style course draws on readings in bioethics, health care, history, medical anthropology, philosophy, and science. Students will engage topics through multimedia resources, short written responses and a comprehensive research paper.', 3, 'W,UD,WE', 'senior,junior,graduate,post-baccalaureate,doctoral', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0),
('BIO 3898', 'Women in Science', 'This course will explore key scientific discoveries with a specific focus on the work of women scientists and the ways in which our understanding of the world has been heavily impacted by successes of these scientists. This course takes both a historical and current perspective to the contributions women scientists have made to their specific fields, including chemistry, physics, engineering, anthropology, and biology. May be repeated for credit 2 times.', 2, 'UD', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0),
('BIO 3896', 'Medical Terminology', 'This course is designed to provide students with an understanding of basic medical terminology so that they can use this vocabulary in the health care setting.  Medical terms associated with body systems, disease processes, laboratory tests, and clinical procedures commonly found in the health care setting will be explored.  Rather than memorizing hundreds or thousands of words we will learn how to break apart a medical word into its parts (e.g. prefix, root, suffix).  Students will read and analyze medical journal articles to practice utilizing medical terminology. Typically offered: Winter.', 2, 'UD', NULL, NULL, '[[[{"course_id": "BIO 2101", "min_grade": "C-", "concurrent_available": false}, {"course_id": "BIO 2102", "min_grade": "C-", "concurrent_available": false}, {"course_id": "BIO 2103", "min_grade": "C-", "concurrent_available": false}]]]', NULL, 0),
('BIO 3899', 'Scientific Literature', 'Students will read, discuss and present recent peer-reviewed journal articles in a selected subdiscipline of biology. The focus of the course will change from quarter to quarter, depending on the interests of the professor and students. Typically offered: Autumn, Spring, Winter. May be repeated for credit 2 times.', 1, 'UD', NULL, NULL, '[[[{"course_id": "BIO 2101", "min_grade": "C-", "concurrent_available": false}, {"course_id": "BIO 2102", "min_grade": "C-", "concurrent_available": false}, {"course_id": "BIO 2103", "min_grade": "C-", "concurrent_available": false}]]]', NULL, 0),
('BIO 4256', 'Environmental Physiology', 'This course focuses on how individuals respond physiologically to their environment especially to maintain homeostasis and acquire nutrients. Topics covered will include circadian rhythms and responses to various stressors (e.g. light, heat, salinity, climate change, hypoxia). Two recurring themes will include discussion of the way in which organisms balance acclimation and adaptation; and the manner in which organisms balance tradeoffs. Typically offered: Autumn, Summer.', 5, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[[[{"course_id": "BIO 2102", "min_grade": "C-", "concurrent_available": false}, {"course_id": "BIO 2103", "min_grade": "C-", "concurrent_available": false}, {"course_id": "MAT 2360", "min_grade": "C-", "concurrent_available": false}]]]', NULL, 1),
('BIO 4320', 'Principles of Development', 'Surveys principles of developmental biology in representative vertebrate and invertebrate models. Required laboratory is devoted to experimental and descriptive approaches to the study of development.  Typically offered: Spring.   Fee(s): Biology Laboratory Fee', 5, 'W,UD', NULL, NULL, '[[[{"course_id": "BIO 2101", "min_grade": "C-", "concurrent_available": false}, {"course_id": "BIO 2102", "min_grade": "C-", "concurrent_available": false}]], [[{"course_id": "BIO 3325", "min_grade": "C-", "concurrent_available": false}]]]', NULL, 0),
('BIO 4320L', 'Principles of Development Lab', 'Lab Component of BIO 4320. Typically offered: Spring.', NULL, 'UD', NULL, NULL, NULL, '["BIO 4320"]', 0),
('BIO 4325', 'Molecular Biology', 'Detailed examination of the molecular mechanisms controlling the replication, regulation and function of nucleic acids in prokaryotes and eukaryotes. Explores foundational principles of molecular genetics, molecular microbiology, genomics and genetic engineering including the central dogma, gene regulation, genomics, biotechnology and associated techniques used by researchers in these fields. Advanced research topics in molecular microbiology will be addressed in the context of an original research project. Includes intensive laboratory.   Fee(s): Biology Laboratory Fee', 5, 'UD,W', NULL, NULL, '[[[{"course_id": "BIO 2101", "min_grade": "C-", "concurrent_available": false}, {"course_id": "BIO 3325", "min_grade": "C-", "concurrent_available": false}]]]', '["BIO 4325L"]', 0),
('BIO 4325L', 'Molecular Biology Lab', 'Lab Component of BIO 4325.', NULL, 'UD', NULL, NULL, NULL, '["BIO 4325"]', 0),
('BIO 4330', 'Evolutionary Mechanisms', 'Explores population genetics as a mechanism of evolutionary change, emphasizing mutation, recombination, and selection. Considers speciation, quantitative genetics, neutral theory, phylogenetic systematics, history, and extinction. Includes discussion of micro-evolutionary and macro-evolutionary changes.  Includes laboratory.   Fee(s): Biology Laboratory Fee', 5, 'UD,W', NULL, '{"excluded_fields": null, "allowed_fields": null, "transfer_only": true}', '[[[{"course_id": "BIO 2103", "min_grade": "C-", "concurrent_available": false}, {"course_id": "BIO 3325", "min_grade": "C-", "concurrent_available": false}, {"course_id": "MAT 2360", "min_grade": "C-", "concurrent_available": false}]]]', NULL, 0),
('BIO 4330L', 'Evolutionary Mechanisms Lab', 'Lab Component of BIO 4330.', NULL, 'UD', NULL, NULL, NULL, '["BIO 4330"]', 0),
('BIO 4352', 'Cell Biology', 'This course will examine eukaryotic cell structure and function. Overarching themes include cellular organelles, interaction of cells with the extracellular environment, cell-cell interactions, cellular movement, and cellular signaling. Includes laboratory.   Fee(s): Biology Laboratory Fee', 5, 'UD', NULL, NULL, '[[[{"course_id": "BIO 3325", "min_grade": "C-", "concurrent_available": false}, {"course_id": "CHM 3373", "min_grade": "C-", "concurrent_available": false}]]]', NULL, 0),
